properties.headline: Beach Hazards Statement issued February 9 at 3:56AM EST until February 9 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Melbourne FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Rough surf and a Moderate Risk of rip currents expected.

* WHERE...Indian River, St. Lucie and Martin Counties.

* WHEN...From 7 AM EST this morning through this evening.

* IMPACTS...The rough surf can knock you down and make you more
susceptible to being caught in the seaward pull of a rip
current. Entering the water is strongly discouraged.
properties.instruction:
Swim near a lifeguard. If caught in a rip current, relax and
float. Don't swim against the current. If able, swim in a
direction following the shoreline. If unable to escape, face the
shore and call or wave for help.

NWSheadline: BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT IN EFFECT FROM 7 AM EST THIS MORNING THROUGH THIS EVENING
